<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 03 at 7:41PM CDT  by NWS Knoxville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southern Sequatchie,
Marion and Hamilton Counties through 930 PM EDT/830 PM CDT/...
At 841 PM EDT/741 PM CDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm near Whitwell, or near Jasper, moving east at 30 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Chattanooga, Jasper, Soddy-Daisy, Signal Mountain, South Pittsburg,
Walden, Lakesite, Whitwell, Kimball and Ridgeside.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
